evals.prompt:
I've got a static HTML page for our new 'Research Hub' landing page — it has a hero section, a 3-column features grid, an FAQ accordion, and a footer CTA. The HTML, CSS, and JS are all in one file. I need this inside WordPress so editors can assign it to a page and it shows up in the Site Editor. The theme is my-theme (kebab-case slug, text domain my-theme). Here's the file:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head><meta charset="UTF-8"><title>Research Hub</title>
<style>
  *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}
  body{font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;background:#0a0a1a;color:#fff}
  .hero{padding:120px 40px;text-align:center;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1a1a2e,#16213e)}
  .hero h1{font-size:3.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem}
  .features{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:2rem;padding:80px 40px}
  .card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05);border-radius:12px;padding:2rem}
  .faq{padding:80px 40px}
  .faq details{border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);padding:1rem 0}
  .cta{padding:120px 40px;text-align:center;background:#e94560}
</style></head>
<body>
  <section class="hero"><h1>Research Hub</h1><p>Science-backed protocols.</p></section>
  <section class="features">
    <div class="card"><h3>Purity</h3><p>99%+ certified.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>Speed</h3><p>Next-day delivery.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>Support</h3><p>Expert guidance.</p></div>
  </section>
  <section class="faq">
    <details><summary>What is the purity?</summary><p>99%+ certified.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How long does delivery take?</summary><p>1-2 working days in the UK.</p></details>
  </section>
  <section class="cta"><h2>Ready to start?</h2><a href="/shop">Shop Now</a></section>
  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.card').forEach(c=>{c.addEventListener('mouseenter',()=>c.style.transform='translateY(-4px)');c.addEventListener('mouseleave',()=>c.style.transform='')});
  </script>
</body></html>
```
